               <sense xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann" xml:id="Dmain">
                  <gramGrp>
                     <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos>
                  </gramGrp> (ut videtur, pro <foreign xml:lang="gez">አርአራይ፡</foreign>) est unus e
                     <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                     <quote>tribus canendi modis</quote>
                  </cit>, quibus Abyssini in cantandis suis hymnis liturgicis utuntur (<lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዕዝል፡</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ግዕዝ፡</foreign>),
                  Deg. (crebro); <foreign xml:lang="gez">፫ዜማ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ግዕዝ፡ ወዕዝል፡ ወአራራይ፡</foreign>
                  <ref cRef="Sx. Genb." loc="11">Sx. Genb. 11</ref>; <ref cRef="Cat. Cod. Ae. Mus. Brit." loc="36 ">Cat. Cod. Ae. Mus. Brit. p. 36
                  </ref>annot. d; <bibl><ptr target="bm:Abbadie1859Cat"/><citedRange unit="page">99</citedRange></bibl>; 
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Abbadie1859Cat"/><citedRange unit="page">119</citedRange></bibl>; Villoteau in
                  description de l’Egypte t. <ref cRef="XIV p." loc="271 ">XIV p. 271 </ref>
                  <lbl expand="sequens">seq.</lbl> – Accuratior ut horum modorum ita omnium musices
                  sacrae vocum technicarum definitio adhuc desideratur. </sense>
               
